WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:04.000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:50.380 --> 00:01:53.460
Parallels

3
00:01:56.970 --> 00:01:59.430
Captain Smoker! Terrible news!

4
00:01:59.430 --> 00:02:01.090
A message from headquarters!

5
00:02:01.090 --> 00:02:06.230
Monkey D. Luffy and his crew
are headed here, to Loguetown!

6
00:02:06.230 --> 00:02:10.650
He just earned a 30-million-belly
bounty in the East Blue!

7
00:02:10.650 --> 00:02:14.110
A 30-million bounty...
Congratulations are in order.

8
00:02:14.110 --> 00:02:18.130
He's so villainous that he even took out
Don Krieg and the fishman Arlong!

9
00:02:18.130 --> 00:02:19.070
Quiet!

10
00:02:24.790 --> 00:02:28.730
Your damn shouting
made it all fall apart.

11
00:02:28.730 --> 00:02:29.580
I'm sorry, sir!

12
00:02:29.580 --> 00:02:32.540
It's no good to let
things stress you out.

13
00:02:32.540 --> 00:02:35.170
I think it's best to do things
at your own pace.

14
00:02:35.170 --> 00:02:36.650
Don't you agree?

15
00:02:36.650 --> 00:02:37.890
Y-Yes, sir!

16
00:02:42.650 --> 00:02:44.130
So, what is this about?

17
00:02:44.130 --> 00:02:46.520
Right! It's about a group of pirates!

18
00:02:46.520 --> 00:02:50.230
It's been reported that they may
show up in town today... Yes!

19
00:02:50.230 --> 00:02:52.070
Why so stressed?

20
00:02:52.070 --> 00:02:54.820
Has a single pirate been able
to escape this town...

21
00:02:54.820 --> 00:02:58.110
since I took command?

22
00:02:58.110 --> 00:02:59.490
N-No, sir...

23
00:02:59.490 --> 00:03:01.360
Then calm the hell down.

24
00:02:59.530 --> 00:03:03.570
Captain "White Hound" Smoker
Marine Headquarters

25
00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:03.570
You're gonna screw up my pace.

26
00:03:03.570 --> 00:03:04.930
Yes, sir...

27
00:03:05.690 --> 00:03:09.530
Reporting, sir! We have word that
pirates have arrived at the port!

28
00:03:09.530 --> 00:03:11.290
Please head there immediately!

29
00:03:11.730 --> 00:03:15.510
It must be Luffy's crew!
They've set foot in town!

30
00:03:15.510 --> 00:03:19.470
Thirty million, huh...? I hope
he at least puts up a fight.

31
00:03:19.470 --> 00:03:20.430
Sir?

32
00:03:20.430 --> 00:03:22.410
Just talking to myself. Forget it.

33
00:03:25.650 --> 00:03:26.810
Don't you wanna look at this?!

34
00:03:28.310 --> 00:03:31.270
"Justice"

35
00:03:31.270 --> 00:03:33.890
Captain! Please give
each unit their orders!

36
00:03:33.890 --> 00:03:34.950
No need.

37
00:03:34.950 --> 00:03:37.780
But he might end up
being pretty strong!

38
00:03:38.870 --> 00:03:40.990
Never mind that. Where's Tashigi?

39
00:03:40.990 --> 00:03:44.230
Y-Yes. She mentioned
she'd be busy this morning,

40
00:03:44.230 --> 00:03:47.190
but that she'd attend the training drills.

41
00:03:47.190 --> 00:03:50.200
That clumsy girl.
Where'd she run off to?

42
00:03:50.200 --> 00:03:52.220
Yay! A triple-scoop ice cream!

43
00:03:52.220 --> 00:03:54.790
Slow it down!
You'll drop them if you run!

44
00:04:02.510 --> 00:04:05.130
C-Captain Smoker!

45
00:04:05.790 --> 00:04:07.110
M-My ice cream...

46
00:04:07.110 --> 00:04:09.560
I-I'm very sorry about my daughter!

47
00:04:09.970 --> 00:04:13.190
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!
I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

48
00:04:14.430 --> 00:04:18.700
Sorry 'bout that.
My pants ate your ice cream.

49
00:04:18.700 --> 00:04:20.930
Here, buy yourself five scoops.

50
00:04:21.870 --> 00:04:22.380
Let's go.

51
00:04:22.380 --> 00:04:23.190
Yes, sir!

52
00:04:24.990 --> 00:04:27.470
Th-Thank you!

53
00:04:27.470 --> 00:04:28.850
Thanks!

54
00:04:33.290 --> 00:04:36.790
Loot everything! Don't leave
a single potato behind!

55
00:04:37.340 --> 00:04:43.300
I, future Pirate King Gally the Crescent, will
need these food supplies on my voyage!

56
00:04:43.300 --> 00:04:46.370
Hand it all over thankfully!

57
00:04:46.370 --> 00:04:47.680
Hey.

58
00:04:47.680 --> 00:04:49.180
Who's in charge here?

59
00:04:50.250 --> 00:04:51.570
What do you want?

60
00:04:51.570 --> 00:04:54.810
So you're Monkey D. Luffy?

61
00:04:55.120 --> 00:05:00.610
I want to test you to see if you're
worthy of setting foot in my town.

62
00:05:00.610 --> 00:05:02.110
What a ripe load of crap!

63
00:05:02.950 --> 00:05:04.150
Get 'im!

64
00:05:13.590 --> 00:05:15.000
Captain Smoker?

65
00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:18.950
Yeah. He's one of the toughest
guys from Marine Headquarters.

66
00:05:18.950 --> 00:05:23.490
This town used to be a hangout
for pirates headed for the Grand Line.

67
00:05:23.490 --> 00:05:28.470
But ever since he took command,
every pirate who's come to town

68
00:05:28.470 --> 00:05:31.060
has wound up behind bars.

69
00:05:31.450 --> 00:05:34.490
His strength is extraordinary.
He's a monster.

70
00:05:34.490 --> 00:05:38.100
They even say he has
devil fruit powers...

71
00:05:38.990 --> 00:05:40.530
Devil fruit powers?!

72
00:05:46.740 --> 00:05:50.870
Incredible, Captain! You captured
Luffy's crew in no time flat!

73
00:05:50.870 --> 00:05:54.630
Are your eyes just for decoration?
This guy obviously isn't Luffy.

74
00:05:54.630 --> 00:05:55.520
What?

75
00:05:55.520 --> 00:05:59.250
The world would end before
this guy is worth 30 million.

76
00:05:59.250 --> 00:06:01.260
Th-Then, where is Luffy?

77
00:06:01.260 --> 00:06:02.930
He'll show up soon enough

78
00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:05.720
The fun's just getting started.

79
00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:07.090
Huh?

80
00:06:07.880 --> 00:06:12.150
And now I'm at the harbor.
How did I get here?

81
00:06:12.150 --> 00:06:13.850
Hey!

82
00:06:14.220 --> 00:06:16.250
Is he one of these guys?

83
00:06:16.250 --> 00:06:18.440
I'm not sure. Probably not...

84
00:06:18.440 --> 00:06:22.570
Perfect timing! Do you know how
to get to the execution platform?

85
00:06:22.570 --> 00:06:23.820
Execution platform...?

86
00:06:23.820 --> 00:06:25.750
I got lost on my way to it...

87
00:06:25.750 --> 00:06:27.910
I've never seen you
around here before.

88
00:06:27.910 --> 00:06:30.530
Yeah! I just arrived on this island!

89
00:06:30.550 --> 00:06:34.860
This town sure is huge! It's way
different from Windmill Village!

90
00:06:34.860 --> 00:06:36.660
So why the execution platform?

91
00:06:36.660 --> 00:06:40.370
I wanna see the place where
the King of the Pirates died!

92
00:06:44.130 --> 00:06:46.420
So you don't know where? Well...

93
00:06:46.430 --> 00:06:49.290
Wait. Follow the smoke.

94
00:06:50.970 --> 00:06:53.680
Oh! That way?! Thanks!

95
00:07:10.570 --> 00:07:12.470
This sucks.

96
00:07:12.470 --> 00:07:17.610
I thought I was headed to the execution
platform, but this can't be the place.

97
00:07:17.610 --> 00:07:20.040
Oh, well. I'll get there sooner or later.

98
00:07:22.830 --> 00:07:24.450
Is it this way?

99
00:07:24.450 --> 00:07:25.580
Let's see...

100
00:07:27.550 --> 00:07:29.790
Gold... Roger?

101
00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:51.950
Do you work here, old guy?

102
00:07:51.950 --> 00:07:55.120
It said "Gold Roger"
on the sign outside.

103
00:07:55.120 --> 00:07:56.830
Is that this place's name?

104
00:07:57.330 --> 00:07:59.040
Scram.

105
00:07:59.040 --> 00:08:02.630
This ain't a place for a runt like you.

106
00:08:02.630 --> 00:08:06.080
Besides, we're closing for good today.

107
00:08:06.080 --> 00:08:07.510
You're going under?

108
00:08:08.050 --> 00:08:11.510
We're not going under!
I'm shutting it down myself!

109
00:08:11.510 --> 00:08:13.050
Now get lost!

110
00:08:13.050 --> 00:08:16.180
I was just curious about the name.

111
00:08:16.180 --> 00:08:18.270
I'm a little lost.

112
00:08:18.270 --> 00:08:21.280
I'm trying to get to
the execution platform...

113
00:08:21.280 --> 00:08:23.310
Can you tell me how to get there?

114
00:08:24.350 --> 00:08:26.270
What's that on the table?

115
00:08:26.270 --> 00:08:29.980
A skull?! It's huge!

116
00:08:29.980 --> 00:08:34.990
This is what became of a guy
who folks called Killer Giant.

117
00:08:34.990 --> 00:08:39.450
He's a fiend who sent hundreds
of pirates to the afterlife.

118
00:08:41.150 --> 00:08:45.210
But Gold Roger sent him to
the afterlife with just one blow.

119
00:08:45.210 --> 00:08:47.030
Gold Roger did?!

120
00:08:47.030 --> 00:08:48.880
With lightning-like speed!

121
00:08:49.240 --> 00:08:51.550
This is the wound he received!

122
00:08:52.690 --> 00:08:55.860
The man may have lived horribly,

123
00:08:55.860 --> 00:08:58.050
but with his dying breath, he muttered,

124
00:08:58.050 --> 00:09:01.620
"Roger... My hat's off to you...

125
00:09:01.620 --> 00:09:04.270
May you be eternally
honored among pirates."

126
00:09:05.350 --> 00:09:07.810
Awesome! That's so cool!

127
00:09:08.180 --> 00:09:12.210
When I heard he had conquered
the Grand Line a little later,

128
00:09:12.210 --> 00:09:16.910
Happiness overcame my surprise,
and my excitement belied my age!

129
00:09:18.550 --> 00:09:24.620
And then, twenty-two years ago today,
Roger died on the execution platform.

130
00:09:25.110 --> 00:09:30.570
And since that day, every cocky upstart
has tossed their hat into the pirate ring.

131
00:09:30.570 --> 00:09:33.650
It was the beginning
of the Great Pirate Era!

132
00:09:34.390 --> 00:09:36.680
But look what's happened!

133
00:09:36.680 --> 00:09:40.430
This town's full of nothing
but cowards and scum now!

134
00:09:40.950 --> 00:09:45.700
Men crazy enough to challenge
that evil sea are all but gone now!

135
00:09:45.700 --> 00:09:49.650
That's why this bar is
closing down for good today.

136
00:09:49.650 --> 00:09:52.020
I'm going to the Grand Line, too!

137
00:09:52.020 --> 00:09:53.030
Huh?!

138
00:09:53.030 --> 00:09:55.800
Gold Roger's so cool...

139
00:09:55.800 --> 00:09:57.990
He's how a pirate should be!

140
00:09:57.990 --> 00:10:00.030
That's why I set out to sea.

141
00:10:00.030 --> 00:10:03.620
I'm gonna go to the Grand Line,
get the One Piece,

142
00:10:03.620 --> 00:10:05.830
and become King of the Pirates!

143
00:10:11.420 --> 00:10:14.260
Those're some mighty big words!

144
00:10:14.260 --> 00:10:16.850
And in this bar, of all places!

145
00:10:16.850 --> 00:10:19.050
I only said what I meant.

146
00:10:20.970 --> 00:10:21.770
Kiddo!

147
00:10:21.770 --> 00:10:26.110
If there're still patrons like you out there,
maybe I'll hold off on closing this place!

148
00:10:26.110 --> 00:10:28.060
How should I know if there are?!

149
00:10:28.060 --> 00:10:31.610
Good point! Of course
you wouldn't know!

150
00:10:31.610 --> 00:10:34.350
I haven't been in this good
a mood since back then...!

151
00:10:34.350 --> 00:10:36.740
I'll treat you to a drink!

152
00:10:37.160 --> 00:10:38.820
I don't drink alcohol.

153
00:10:40.010 --> 00:10:42.120
Sure! I have just the thing!

154
00:10:43.630 --> 00:10:47.950
Let's have a toast!
To the eternal King of the Pirates!

155
00:10:51.570 --> 00:10:53.590
To the eternal King of the Pirates!

156
00:11:05.890 --> 00:11:09.570
Amazing! That's
an elephant bluefin tuna!

157
00:11:09.570 --> 00:11:13.120
That's right! It probably got
mixed in from the southern ocean.

158
00:11:13.120 --> 00:11:15.340
I caught it with a pole and line!

159
00:11:15.340 --> 00:11:16.780
A pole and line?!

160
00:11:17.610 --> 00:11:19.740
An elephant bluefin tuna...

161
00:11:20.100 --> 00:11:22.230
Okay, then, haul it away.

162
00:11:22.230 --> 00:11:23.010
– Okay!
– Okay!

163
00:11:23.010 --> 00:11:24.800
H-Hold on a second!

164
00:11:24.800 --> 00:11:25.330
Hm?

165
00:11:25.330 --> 00:11:28.200
How much is it?! Let me buy it!

166
00:11:29.730 --> 00:11:32.580
I bought a lot, a heck of a lot!

167
00:11:33.050 --> 00:11:36.880
Now my preparations to be a brave
warrior of the sea are complete!

168
00:11:36.880 --> 00:11:39.490
All I've got left is...

169
00:11:39.490 --> 00:11:43.140
Oh, yeah! I forgot the most
important thing. Goggles.

170
00:11:43.590 --> 00:11:47.870
The best goggles for the best marksman!
Does it get anymore basic than that?!

171
00:11:47.870 --> 00:11:50.590
Sparing no expense on
the best goggles around

172
00:11:50.590 --> 00:11:54.100
is the very essence of
being the best marksman!

173
00:11:54.100 --> 00:11:56.030
Goggles! Goggles!

174
00:12:06.070 --> 00:12:09.870
These ones! These goggles!
They're just perfect!

175
00:12:09.870 --> 00:12:10.790
Ma'am!

176
00:12:10.790 --> 00:12:14.790
You've got a good eye! They're
the latest model from the North Blue!

177
00:12:14.790 --> 00:12:18.800
I got 'em from an import vessel that
only leaves the Marines once a year!

178
00:12:18.800 --> 00:12:20.300
What's the matter? No money?

179
00:12:20.870 --> 00:12:23.970
I only deal in cash,
so what's it gonna be?

180
00:12:23.970 --> 00:12:26.090
N-No, it's... Oh!
Right! My backpack...

181
00:12:26.090 --> 00:12:28.100
I'll take these goggles, please!

182
00:12:28.100 --> 00:12:30.130
My! What a cute little girl!

183
00:12:30.130 --> 00:12:31.960
Yes, yes, yes, yes! You're in luck!

184
00:12:31.960 --> 00:12:35.070
This is the only pair in town!

185
00:12:36.190 --> 00:12:38.020
Hold it right there!

186
00:12:38.020 --> 00:12:39.610
I saw them first, so–

187
00:12:39.610 --> 00:12:40.740
Huh?

188
00:12:41.620 --> 00:12:42.070
Hm?

189
00:12:42.590 --> 00:12:44.240
Butt out, old man!

190
00:12:44.240 --> 00:12:45.630
O...?!

191
00:12:48.390 --> 00:12:49.490
Old man?

192
00:12:51.540 --> 00:12:54.010
Stop! Stop right there, you!

193
00:12:54.010 --> 00:12:57.060
Listen! First things first!
There's no way I'm an old man!

194
00:12:57.060 --> 00:12:59.290
I'm more like a big brother. Got it?

195
00:12:59.290 --> 00:13:01.320
Huh?! What're you
talking about, old man?!

196
00:13:01.320 --> 00:13:03.290
Dammit, you said it again!

197
00:13:03.290 --> 00:13:05.090
Just gimme those goggles already!

198
00:13:05.090 --> 00:13:05.970
Huh?!

199
00:13:06.820 --> 00:13:09.050
You got a problem?! Huh?!

200
00:13:09.050 --> 00:13:11.840
Keep up yer damn complainin'
and I'll call the Marines!

201
00:13:11.840 --> 00:13:12.770
M-Marines?

202
00:13:12.770 --> 00:13:16.910
Yep! I'm friends with
a Marine captain in this town!

203
00:13:16.910 --> 00:13:18.900
The old smoky man!

204
00:13:18.900 --> 00:13:20.750
Wh-Who is this girl?

205
00:13:22.170 --> 00:13:23.940
Don't you know who I am?!

206
00:13:23.940 --> 00:13:27.450
I'm the great Captain Usopp!
I destroyed Arlong's Fishman Pirates!

207
00:13:27.820 --> 00:13:31.130
It was a dire battle! The fishmen had
me surrounded 200—no, 300 to 1!

208
00:13:31.130 --> 00:13:35.410
All alone, I punched, threw, stomped,
kicked, and tore them all up!

209
00:13:35.410 --> 00:13:40.380
Thanks to that, I now have
a 30-million-belly bounty on my head!

210
00:13:41.270 --> 00:13:43.200
I see. 30 million...

211
00:13:43.200 --> 00:13:45.050
Yep! That's right!

212
00:13:45.050 --> 00:13:46.260
Papa!

213
00:13:46.260 --> 00:13:48.680
Papa?! Now you're calling me Pa–

214
00:13:48.680 --> 00:13:49.360
Ah!

215
00:13:49.360 --> 00:13:51.720
Here's a present for you, Papa!

216
00:13:51.720 --> 00:13:53.970
Happy birthday!

217
00:13:53.970 --> 00:13:56.330
Oh, Carol...

218
00:13:59.270 --> 00:14:04.120
What a considerate little angel
you are! I love you, Carol!

219
00:14:04.120 --> 00:14:06.110
And I love you, Papa!

220
00:14:06.480 --> 00:14:09.130
Wh-What's with this family?

221
00:14:11.530 --> 00:14:15.340
But listen! That asshole old man there
is trying to swipe your present!

222
00:14:15.340 --> 00:14:19.040
Now, now! "Asshole" is a bad word.

223
00:14:19.040 --> 00:14:22.000
You should mind your manners, okay?

224
00:14:23.450 --> 00:14:27.590
You wouldn't happen to be picking on
my adorable Carol, would you?

225
00:14:27.590 --> 00:14:30.300
P-P-Picking on...?

226
00:14:30.680 --> 00:14:31.720
That's not all!

227
00:14:31.740 --> 00:14:33.130
Huh?

228
00:14:35.090 --> 00:14:38.390
You have a bounty of
30 million belly, I hear?

229
00:14:38.930 --> 00:14:40.570
Let's see here...

230
00:14:40.570 --> 00:14:42.690
Are those the new wanted posters?

231
00:14:42.690 --> 00:14:45.390
Yeah, I got 'em from
the outpost just now...

232
00:14:45.390 --> 00:14:47.200
Six hundred thousand...

233
00:14:47.200 --> 00:14:49.330
One million three hundred thousand...

234
00:14:49.330 --> 00:14:51.160
Seven hundred thousand... Huh?

235
00:14:51.990 --> 00:14:53.950
Thirty million... Straw Hat Luffy?

236
00:14:54.340 --> 00:14:57.450
For a starting bounty to be this high...

237
00:14:57.950 --> 00:14:59.250
Hold it, boy.

238
00:15:00.250 --> 00:15:02.060
Y-Y-Yes?!

239
00:15:02.060 --> 00:15:03.400
No, you see, sir,

240
00:15:03.400 --> 00:15:07.350
I'm obviously not the person
on that poster! I was just lying!

241
00:15:07.350 --> 00:15:10.720
My silly little prank was
a great success! Well, bye!

242
00:15:11.680 --> 00:15:13.090
That's you, isn't it?

243
00:15:13.850 --> 00:15:17.360
Th-Th-That's right!
It sure is! That's me, all right!

244
00:15:17.360 --> 00:15:18.650
But know this!

245
00:15:18.650 --> 00:15:22.690
If you lay a hand on me,
my captain Luffy won't stand for it!

246
00:15:22.690 --> 00:15:26.610
He's an evil, cold-blooded,
devilish man!

247
00:15:26.610 --> 00:15:29.280
No one's ever crossed him
and lived to tell the tale.

248
00:15:29.660 --> 00:15:33.450
You've got a kid, so you really
ought to value your life more...

249
00:15:33.450 --> 00:15:35.580
I see. It doesn't sound worth it.

250
00:15:36.550 --> 00:15:42.350
A bounty of 30 million makes it clear
this Luffy fellow is no ordinary man.

251
00:15:42.350 --> 00:15:45.530
Papa! You're obviously way stronger!

252
00:15:45.530 --> 00:15:47.550
You're the strongest in the world!

253
00:15:47.550 --> 00:15:49.250
Carol, it's all right.

254
00:15:49.250 --> 00:15:53.770
As long as I earn enough
to provide for us, I'm happy.

255
00:15:53.770 --> 00:15:56.970
You're far more important to me
than being the world's greatest!

256
00:15:56.970 --> 00:15:58.060
Papa...

257
00:15:59.450 --> 00:16:02.810
He's actually backing off
after I said all that!

258
00:16:02.810 --> 00:16:04.520
Alright! In that case...!

259
00:16:04.520 --> 00:16:07.230
So you realize how terrifying I am?!

260
00:16:07.230 --> 00:16:10.240
Take my advice! Just hand
those goggles over to me!

261
00:16:10.240 --> 00:16:11.280
Huh?!

262
00:16:11.280 --> 00:16:16.110
Don't worry! I'll pay for 'em!
So just give 'em here!

263
00:16:16.110 --> 00:16:20.530
Why the hell would you say that
when he was about to let you–

264
00:16:20.530 --> 00:16:21.450
Papa?

265
00:16:21.450 --> 00:16:22.750
Then let's do this.

266
00:16:23.200 --> 00:16:26.750
I assume you have no problem
with us settling this in a fair fight?

267
00:16:26.750 --> 00:16:27.700
A fight...?

268
00:16:27.700 --> 00:16:28.960
Here!

269
00:16:28.960 --> 00:16:32.760
A fight...?! Y-You're not
talking about a duel, are you?!

270
00:16:32.760 --> 00:16:35.720
If you win, the goggles are yours.

271
00:16:37.450 --> 00:16:40.150
One, two, three, four,
five, six... thirty pistols?!

272
00:16:40.150 --> 00:16:42.180
D-Don't tell me you're...

273
00:16:42.510 --> 00:16:44.690
Daddy the Father?!

274
00:16:44.690 --> 00:16:46.030
A duel!

275
00:16:46.030 --> 00:16:47.110
There's gonna be a duel!

276
00:16:47.110 --> 00:16:49.230
It's a duel with Daddy the Father!

277
00:16:49.230 --> 00:16:51.690
Did he say Daddy the Father?

278
00:16:52.550 --> 00:16:56.050
Daddy the Father is the greatest
gunslinger bounty hunter!

279
00:16:56.050 --> 00:16:58.210
Everyone in the East Blue knows that!

280
00:16:58.210 --> 00:17:03.040
So what kind of idiot would
challenge him to a duel?!

281
00:17:06.630 --> 00:17:07.880
Oh, that kind.

282
00:17:07.880 --> 00:17:09.800
Good luck, long nose!

283
00:17:09.800 --> 00:17:13.850
Don't worry if he beats you!
We've already dug your grave!

284
00:17:15.380 --> 00:17:19.390
H-How did things turn out like this?
What's wrong with me?!

285
00:17:19.390 --> 00:17:22.450
The rules are simple. We both
walk ten paces and then shoot.

286
00:17:22.450 --> 00:17:23.320
Y-Yeah...

287
00:17:23.320 --> 00:17:25.030
What are you doing?!

288
00:17:25.030 --> 00:17:25.970
Nami!

289
00:17:25.970 --> 00:17:29.060
Facing Daddy the Father in
a duel... Have you lost your mind?!

290
00:17:29.060 --> 00:17:32.280
Sh-Shut up! It just kinda happened,
so shut up and watch!

291
00:17:32.280 --> 00:17:35.280
You get one shot. Are you ready?

292
00:17:35.280 --> 00:17:37.240
Yeah.

293
00:17:36.290 --> 00:17:37.240
Yeah...

294
00:17:45.470 --> 00:17:46.470
One!

295
00:17:48.030 --> 00:17:49.420
Two!

296
00:17:49.970 --> 00:17:51.030
Three!

297
00:17:52.190 --> 00:17:53.230
Four!

298
00:17:54.010 --> 00:17:55.010
Five!

299
00:17:56.370 --> 00:17:58.590
This is bad... Really bad...

300
00:17:58.590 --> 00:18:01.680
There's no way I can possibly
beat Daddy the Father...

301
00:18:01.680 --> 00:18:02.680
Six!

302
00:18:04.530 --> 00:18:07.690
Am I going to die here?!
This can't be happening!

303
00:18:08.040 --> 00:18:08.650
Seven!

304
00:18:10.110 --> 00:18:12.700
I just started my adventure!

305
00:18:12.700 --> 00:18:16.990
I haven't even gained any courage
or manliness or anything yet!

306
00:18:18.030 --> 00:18:18.740
Eight!

307
00:18:20.870 --> 00:18:21.950
Later!

308
00:18:38.190 --> 00:18:39.060
Papa!

309
00:18:39.060 --> 00:18:41.220
You're amazing, Papa! You're so cool!

310
00:18:41.220 --> 00:18:42.940
Man, how pathetic.

311
00:18:42.940 --> 00:18:44.390
What a lame duel.

312
00:18:44.390 --> 00:18:48.600
I thought he'd have more guts
than that. What a disappointment.

313
00:18:48.910 --> 00:18:51.270
Who do you think
you are, trying to cheat?!

314
00:18:51.270 --> 00:18:55.050
You cowardly weakling!
Can't you at least fight honestly?!

315
00:18:55.050 --> 00:18:59.150
I-I'm sorry! Forgive me!
I'm just a lowly, pathetic man!

316
00:18:59.150 --> 00:19:02.910
You'd get nothing out of
killing someone like me!

317
00:19:02.910 --> 00:19:03.620
Right?! Right?!

318
00:19:04.170 --> 00:19:05.830
Can't you just let me go?

319
00:19:07.230 --> 00:19:08.530
W-Wait!

320
00:19:08.530 --> 00:19:09.660
Nami!

321
00:19:09.660 --> 00:19:13.370
R-Right! If it's money
you want, she has plenty!

322
00:19:13.370 --> 00:19:16.330
Just please don't shoot me!
Please spare my life!

323
00:19:16.330 --> 00:19:17.340
Hold on, now!

324
00:19:17.700 --> 00:19:20.430
Now you're groveling behind a woman?

325
00:19:21.290 --> 00:19:22.930
Anyway–

326
00:19:23.430 --> 00:19:25.490
No! Forget what I just said!

327
00:19:25.490 --> 00:19:27.970
She's an innocent bystander!

328
00:19:27.970 --> 00:19:31.410
I can't drag her into this,
even if it means I get shot!

329
00:19:31.410 --> 00:19:32.340
Usopp...

330
00:19:32.340 --> 00:19:34.150
Please! I beg you!

331
00:19:34.150 --> 00:19:35.660
"Usopp..."

332
00:19:35.660 --> 00:19:37.610
Kid, your name is Usopp?

333
00:19:37.940 --> 00:19:38.610
Yeah.

334
00:19:39.490 --> 00:19:41.220
It couldn't be...

335
00:19:41.220 --> 00:19:46.120
Do you know a man named
Yasopp of the Red Hair Pirates?

336
00:19:46.120 --> 00:19:49.820
Yasopp? That's my old man's name.

337
00:19:49.820 --> 00:19:52.620
Y-You've met my dad before?!

338
00:19:53.050 --> 00:19:55.500
Then you are his son...

339
00:19:56.510 --> 00:19:57.340
Papa?

340
00:19:58.350 --> 00:20:03.770
I've never once told a soul
what happened on that day,

341
00:20:03.770 --> 00:20:06.140
but I'll make an exception.

342
00:20:06.140 --> 00:20:11.950
It happened at a hot,
dry port town, much like this one.

343
00:20:11.950 --> 00:20:15.480
Let's do it, Ensign Masterson!
We each get one shot!

344
00:20:15.480 --> 00:20:19.070
One! Two! Three!

345
00:20:32.530 --> 00:20:37.420
Kill me! Now that I've lost a duel,
I have no reason to live...

346
00:20:41.390 --> 00:20:43.090
What are you doing?

347
00:20:43.090 --> 00:20:44.510
Your daughter?

348
00:20:44.510 --> 00:20:45.900
Give it back...

349
00:20:45.900 --> 00:20:50.180
An ensign in the Marines, carefully
treasuring something like this...

350
00:20:50.180 --> 00:20:51.540
You must really spoil her.

351
00:20:51.540 --> 00:20:54.570
Don't lecture me, you filthy pirate!

352
00:20:54.570 --> 00:20:56.070
Fine by me!

353
00:20:57.480 --> 00:20:59.810
You were great, Yasopp!

354
00:20:59.810 --> 00:21:01.230
It was nothing.

355
00:21:01.230 --> 00:21:03.950
This wound really shows
off my inexperience.

356
00:21:03.950 --> 00:21:06.410
But you took on Daddy Masterson!

357
00:21:06.410 --> 00:21:08.950
You won because you're you!

358
00:21:08.950 --> 00:21:11.740
Yeah, we never would've
stood a chance...

359
00:21:12.500 --> 00:21:14.090
Thanks, Boss!

360
00:21:14.090 --> 00:21:18.710
I appreciate you watching
the duel without saying a thing.

361
00:21:23.750 --> 00:21:26.300
That's the stuff!
You want some, Ensign?

362
00:21:29.850 --> 00:21:31.520
Family, huh?

363
00:21:31.520 --> 00:21:34.810
Family's not so bad.
But I'm no good at it.

364
00:21:34.810 --> 00:21:35.870
Huh?

365
00:21:35.870 --> 00:21:39.030
I've got a son of my own.
His name's Usopp.

366
00:21:39.030 --> 00:21:40.680
Haven't seen him in years now.

367
00:21:40.680 --> 00:21:44.370
I hit the high seas around
the time he was a toddler.

368
00:21:44.370 --> 00:21:48.110
Why? Do you not love your son?

369
00:21:48.750 --> 00:21:50.870
It wasn't about that.

370
00:21:52.080 --> 00:21:54.290
It was about the flag...

371
00:21:54.290 --> 00:21:56.970
I heard the call of the Jolly Roger.

372
00:21:56.970 --> 00:21:59.150
You tell 'im, Yasopp!

373
00:22:04.380 --> 00:22:05.800
Now, then...

374
00:22:08.390 --> 00:22:11.890
There's nothing I can do for my son.

375
00:22:11.890 --> 00:22:15.980
Even one hopeless parent
like me is one too many.

376
00:22:16.870 --> 00:22:19.360
Always stay by your daughter's side.

377
00:22:19.360 --> 00:22:21.230
You can't let her feel lonely.

378
00:22:21.250 --> 00:22:24.270
Though I'm in no position to talk!

379
00:22:29.270 --> 00:22:32.790
I lost our duel! Yasopp! Finish me!

380
00:22:32.790 --> 00:22:35.180
Don't give me your lousy pity!

381
00:22:35.180 --> 00:22:36.690
Forget it!

382
00:22:36.690 --> 00:22:40.750
You Marines might hang us by
our necks the moment you catch us,

383
00:22:40.750 --> 00:22:44.630
but we pirates are free to kill
or spare who we please!

384
00:22:44.630 --> 00:22:45.800
So long!

385
00:22:59.100 --> 00:23:03.770
Papa! You lost to a pirate,
and he spared your life?!

386
00:23:03.770 --> 00:23:08.670
But that's amazing!
Your dad must be really skilled!

387
00:23:08.670 --> 00:23:09.320
Usopp?

388
00:23:09.650 --> 00:23:11.280
Would you normally...?

389
00:23:11.280 --> 00:23:14.150
Would you normally tell
some pathetic boy like me...

390
00:23:14.150 --> 00:23:16.910
a shameless story about
having your life spared?!

391
00:23:18.690 --> 00:23:22.350
You told me that to give me courage!

392
00:23:22.350 --> 00:23:25.570
Most people would be too
ashamed to tell a story like that,

393
00:23:25.570 --> 00:23:28.760
but you told me even though
you'd become way less cool!

394
00:23:29.220 --> 00:23:33.940
Regardless of how brave you
showed my old man to be. Right?!

395
00:23:33.940 --> 00:23:36.890
No weakling or coward
could do what you just did!

396
00:23:38.470 --> 00:23:41.430
Carol! Your dad is
the bravest man alive!

397
00:23:41.430 --> 00:23:43.950
You can find strong guys anywhere!

398
00:23:43.950 --> 00:23:48.050
But I've never seen a man as
strong and kind as your dad before!

399
00:23:50.130 --> 00:23:57.450
I... I can't throw in the towel! I gotta
be brave, or I'll shame your dad!

400
00:23:57.450 --> 00:23:59.430
Daddy! Give me a chance!

401
00:23:59.430 --> 00:24:02.310
Face me in another life-or-death duel!

402
00:24:02.310 --> 00:24:03.960
I won't cheat this time!

403
00:24:09.690 --> 00:24:12.530
All right. This will be
our real showdown.

404
00:24:12.530 --> 00:24:15.090
Choose the weapon you're
most comfortable with.

405
00:24:18.260 --> 00:24:21.680
Good. Now, then. Let's see...

406
00:24:25.150 --> 00:24:27.740
Try and hit that weather vane.

407
00:24:27.740 --> 00:24:29.910
That weather vane? Over there?!

408
00:24:32.190 --> 00:24:34.200
Miss it, and...

409
00:24:34.200 --> 00:24:37.040
Y-Yeah! You can shoot
me right through the heart!

410
00:24:37.040 --> 00:24:37.700
Usopp!

411
00:24:39.070 --> 00:24:42.370
My life is on the
line for real this time!

412
00:24:46.790 --> 00:24:48.190
There's...

413
00:24:48.190 --> 00:24:51.510
There's no way he can shoot
that far with that thing...

414
00:25:12.230 --> 00:25:13.640
You missed!

415
00:25:13.640 --> 00:25:16.360
No, Papa! Don't shoot him! Papa!

416
00:25:18.750 --> 00:25:22.110
I can't shoot him. Usopp shot
right through its crown!

417
00:25:23.890 --> 00:25:26.330
H-He really did!
Right through the crown!

418
00:25:27.410 --> 00:25:28.830
Usopp!

419
00:25:28.830 --> 00:25:32.300
You're an excellent shot.
I'd expect no less of Yasopp's son.

420
00:25:32.300 --> 00:25:34.300
Never forget that bravery.

421
00:25:34.300 --> 00:25:38.260
You'll be just like your
old man someday!

422
00:25:40.370 --> 00:25:43.870
Go to the Grand Line.
I'm certain Yasopp is there.

423
00:25:43.870 --> 00:25:44.850
Daddy...

424
00:25:47.310 --> 00:25:49.510
You're pretty good, old man!

425
00:25:49.510 --> 00:25:50.810
Aren't these...?

426
00:25:51.410 --> 00:25:53.500
It's okay! See ya!

427
00:25:53.500 --> 00:25:54.570
Papa!

428
00:25:54.570 --> 00:25:56.680
Carol, you should know better.

429
00:25:56.680 --> 00:25:58.910
It's bad manners to say, "See ya!"

430
00:25:58.910 --> 00:26:00.950
Right! Sorry, Papa!

431
00:26:00.950 --> 00:26:04.700
I'm going to grow up to be a proper
lady worthy of being your daughter!

432
00:26:04.700 --> 00:26:05.940
So will you forgive me?

433
00:26:05.940 --> 00:26:09.170
You're already about as
proper as they come!

434
00:26:09.170 --> 00:26:10.540
I'll be even more proper!

435
00:26:10.540 --> 00:26:13.150
Even if people consider him a disgrace,

436
00:26:13.150 --> 00:26:17.130
he's only ever fought to
protect the one he loves.

437
00:26:17.130 --> 00:26:21.170
I'm going to be
a brave man like Daddy!

438
00:26:21.170 --> 00:26:25.810
I'm gonna become a real warrior
and stand before my dad someday!

439
00:26:27.670 --> 00:26:29.150
I know it!

440
00:26:37.970 --> 00:26:38.860
You?!

441
00:26:39.200 --> 00:26:41.230
That's quite the warm weclome...

442
00:26:42.230 --> 00:26:43.950
and I'm a regular, too.

443
00:26:44.830 --> 00:26:47.770
I'm not the one you
should be angry with.

444
00:26:47.770 --> 00:26:50.500
I only come here as a loyal customer.

445
00:26:50.500 --> 00:26:54.340
It's the pirates' fault that
they're all cowards these days.

446
00:26:57.030 --> 00:26:59.430
You had a customer? That's rare.

447
00:27:01.090 --> 00:27:03.850
I'd like some rum.

448
00:27:03.850 --> 00:27:06.050
There's no booze here for you!

449
00:27:06.050 --> 00:27:07.980
Don't be so cold-hearted.

450
00:27:07.980 --> 00:27:10.730
Today's a special day.

451
00:27:12.390 --> 00:27:13.630
Wouldn't you agree?

452
00:27:18.450 --> 00:27:19.990
That's the stuff...

453
00:27:22.010 --> 00:27:25.430
I can still see it like it was yesterday...

454
00:27:26.730 --> 00:27:29.120
How Roger looked at the very end...

455
00:27:29.120 --> 00:27:32.450
It was a humid afternoon,
just like today...

456
00:27:35.230 --> 00:27:38.250
Hands shackled, he was led down
the main street toward the plaza

457
00:27:38.250 --> 00:27:40.230
where the execution platform stood.

458
00:27:40.230 --> 00:27:43.710
Yet, he marched down it
like a triumphant general.

459
00:28:12.750 --> 00:28:15.380
Wealth, fame, power...

460
00:28:15.930 --> 00:28:20.080
Gold Roger obtained everything
the world had to offer.

461
00:28:20.080 --> 00:28:22.550
Even though he was
walking toward death,

462
00:28:22.550 --> 00:28:25.850
he was the embodiment
of a pride-filled king...

463
00:28:26.650 --> 00:28:29.310
Inherited will...

464
00:28:29.310 --> 00:28:32.830
the tides of time,
and humanity's dreams...

465
00:28:32.830 --> 00:28:36.130
As long as people seek freedom,

466
00:28:36.130 --> 00:28:39.570
these things will never cease to be.

467
00:28:48.010 --> 00:28:50.030
Do you have any last words?!

468
00:28:52.070 --> 00:28:56.160
Do you mind removing these?
They itch like you wouldn't believe.

469
00:28:56.160 --> 00:28:57.430
I can't do that!

470
00:28:57.430 --> 00:28:59.090
You think I would run?

471
00:29:00.490 --> 00:29:03.050
Guess I'm on my own.

472
00:29:07.510 --> 00:29:10.330
All right, let's get this over with.

473
00:29:26.730 --> 00:29:28.200
Hey, Pirate King!

474
00:29:29.490 --> 00:29:31.870
Where did you hide
all the treasure you found?!

475
00:29:31.870 --> 00:29:34.120
Is it in the Grand Line?!

476
00:29:34.530 --> 00:29:38.580
You found it, didn't you?!
That legendary treasure!

477
00:29:38.580 --> 00:29:40.040
Shut up, you!

478
00:29:40.040 --> 00:29:42.550
That great treasure!

479
00:29:43.630 --> 00:29:47.490
The One Piece!

480
00:29:57.100 --> 00:29:58.690
My treasure?

481
00:29:58.690 --> 00:30:00.010
Who said you could speak?!

482
00:30:00.010 --> 00:30:02.150
It's yours, if you can find it!

483
00:30:02.150 --> 00:30:07.150
Everything is right where I left it!

484
00:30:05.610 --> 00:30:07.150
Execute!

485
00:30:41.650 --> 00:30:44.690
That's how it all began...

486
00:30:46.630 --> 00:30:48.110
Hey!

487
00:30:48.110 --> 00:30:51.390
A new wanted poster!
Put it up somewhere noticeable!

488
00:30:52.650 --> 00:30:55.290
C-Captain Smoker!
Pardon the intrusion, sir!

489
00:30:59.410 --> 00:31:00.460
U-Umm...

490
00:31:01.150 --> 00:31:02.670
That straw hat...

491
00:31:03.070 --> 00:31:05.550
It was Monkey D. Luffy!

492
00:31:11.610 --> 00:31:12.510
There it is...

493
00:31:15.170 --> 00:31:19.790
The place where the
greatest pirate in history died...

494
00:31:21.270 --> 00:31:22.930
The place where it all began...
